14/*
15 * 32 bit Fowler/Noll/Vo FNV-1a hash code with modification for BIND
16 */

32static uint32_t fnv_offset_basis;
33static isc_once_t fnv_once = ISC_ONCE_INIT;
34static bool fnv_initialized = false;

71static void
72fnv_initialize(void) {
73 /*
74 * This function should not leave fnv_offset_basis set to
75 * 0. Also, after this function has been called, if it is called
76 * again, it should not change fnv_offset_basis.
77 */
78 while (fnv_offset_basis == 0) {
79 fnv_offset_basis = isc_random32();
80 }
81
82 fnv_initialized = true;
83}
84
85const void *
86isc_hash_get_initializer(void) {
87 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(!fnv_initialized))
88 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&fnv_once, fnv_initialize) ==
89 ISC_R_SUCCESS);
90
91 return (&fnv_offset_basis);
92}
93
94void
95isc_hash_set_initializer(const void *initializer) {
96 REQUIRE(initializer != NULL);
97
98 /*
99 * Ensure that fnv_initialize() is not called after
100 * isc_hash_set_initializer() is called.
101 */
102 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(!fnv_initialized))
103 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&fnv_once, fnv_initialize) ==
104 ISC_R_SUCCESS);
105
106 fnv_offset_basis = *((const unsigned int *)initializer);
107}
108
109#define FNV_32_PRIME ((uint32_t)0x01000193)
110
111uint32_t
112isc_hash_function(const void *data, size_t length, bool case_sensitive,
113 const uint32_t *previous_hashp)
114{
115 uint32_t hval;
116 const unsigned char *bp;
117 const unsigned char *be;
118
119 REQUIRE(length == 0 || data != NULL);
120
121 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(!fnv_initialized)) {
122 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&fnv_once, fnv_initialize) ==
123 ISC_R_SUCCESS);
124 }
125
126 hval = ISC_UNLIKELY(previous_hashp != NULL) ? *previous_hashp
127 : fnv_offset_basis;
128
129 if (length == 0) {
130 return (hval);
131 }
132
133 bp = (const unsigned char *)data;
134 be = bp + length;
135
136 /*
137 * Fowler-Noll-Vo FNV-1a hash function.
138 *
139 * NOTE: A random FNV offset basis is used by default to avoid
140 * collision attacks as the hash function is reversible. This
141 * makes the mapping non-deterministic, but the distribution in
142 * the domain is still uniform.
143 */
144
145 if (case_sensitive) {
146 while (bp < be) {
147 hval ^= *bp++;
148 hval *= FNV_32_PRIME;
149 }
150 } else {
151 while (bp < be) {
152 hval ^= maptolower[*bp++];
153 hval *= FNV_32_PRIME;
154 }
155 }
156
157 return (hval);
158}
159
160uint32_t
161isc_hash_function_reverse(const void *data, size_t length, bool case_sensitive,
162 const uint32_t *previous_hashp)
163{
164 uint32_t hval;
165 const unsigned char *bp;
166 const unsigned char *be;
167
168 REQUIRE(length == 0 || data != NULL);
169
170 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(!fnv_initialized)) {
171 RUNTIME_CHECK(isc_once_do(&fnv_once, fnv_initialize) ==
172 ISC_R_SUCCESS);
173 }
174
175 hval = ISC_UNLIKELY(previous_hashp != NULL) ? *previous_hashp
176 : fnv_offset_basis;
177
178 if (length == 0) {
179 return (hval);
180 }
181
182 bp = (const unsigned char *)data;
183 be = bp + length;
184
185 /*
186 * Fowler-Noll-Vo FNV-1a hash function.
187 *
188 * NOTE: A random FNV offset basis is used by default to avoid
189 * collision attacks as the hash function is reversible. This
190 * makes the mapping non-deterministic, but the distribution in
191 * the domain is still uniform.
192 */
193
194 if (case_sensitive) {
195 while (--be >= bp) {
196 hval ^= *be;
197 hval *= FNV_32_PRIME;
198 }
199 } else {
200 while (--be >= bp) {
201 hval ^= maptolower[*be];
202 hval *= FNV_32_PRIME;
203 }
204 }
205
206 return (hval);
207}
